# To show a list of your current shell aliases:
alias

# To alias `ls -l` to `ll`:
alias ll='ls -l'

# To remove alias:
unalias ll

######################################################
zsh
global -g flag. aggressive. it replaces all occurrences of the alias name with the specified command.
  alias -g qId="--query id -o tsv"
   az aks show -n myaks2020 -g rg-demo --query id -o tsv
   az aks show -n myaks2020 -g rg-demo qId	

Suffix Aliases
 -s flag.  can launch files with a specific extension (or suffix) in your favorite tool.
	alias -s md=code  #opens md files with vscode type sample.md-> code smaple.md
	alias -s {cs,ts,html}=code
